rComments: I had professor Levasseur in person for the first class she ever taught and boy was she a joy. Genuinely cares about you and wants you to succeed. Would recommend her to anyone and would take another FLS class with her if I have the chance!

Ms. Levasseur is easily one of the best profs I've had. She genuinely cares and is always willing to hear you out and help. The class itself was pretty easy, attendance is quite important because there are a lot of group assignments.

The class was really straight forward, if you paid attention in the class you will do well. We didn't use any textbooks but we read a lot of articles which were later used in the exams. She can be a tougher grader but that's because she gives clear expectations to what she wants in her rubrics, so my suggestion follow them to a T!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback']
